    "parameters": [],
    "return_type": "",
    "exceptions": [],
    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "By default, when reading from /dev/random, getrandom() blocks if no random bytes are available, and when reading from /dev/urandom, it blocks if the entropy pool has not yet been initialized. If the GRND_NONBLOCK flag is set, then getrandom() does not block in these cases, but instead immediately raises BlockingIOError. Added in version 3.6."
    },
    "example": "",
